arrangements immediately."

04:14.722 --> 04:15.523
[TYPEWRITER CARRIAGE GRATES]

04:16.490 --> 04:17.391
[TYPING CONTINUES]

04:31.071 --> 04:32.005
[GRUNTS]

04:34.608 --> 04:35.476
[TYPING CONTINUES]

04:39.012 --> 04:39.880
[DRUMROLL]

04:41.649 --> 04:42.716
[CYMBALS CRASH]

04:42.750 --> 04:43.784
[APPLAUDING]

04:48.956 --> 04:50.791
MAYOR: The hardworking
citizens of Northfork

04:51.892 --> 04:54.027
will be able to have
their much-needed power.

04:55.529 --> 04:56.464
As well as

04:58.065 --> 04:59.567
the pleasure of the recreation

05:00.768 --> 05:02.436
that this body of water
will provide.

05:03.504 --> 05:04.372
Let me add this.

05:05.906 --> 05:07.040
The good people of Northfork

05:08.275 --> 05:10.511
will be able to have
their cake and eat it too.

05:11.612 --> 05:12.546
[APPLAUSE]

05:13.814 --> 05:14.848
Two, three...

05:14.882 --> 05:15.949
[BAND PLAYING]

05:20.388 --> 05:21.054
[AIRPLANE WHIZZING]

05:24.892 --> 05:26.660
MAN: Where are we going
to start? Right in here?

05:26.694 --> 05:28.128
Where should we start?
MAN 2: Let's start
right in here.

05:28.161 --> 05:29.062
[CAMERA SNAPS]

05:31.699 --> 05:32.833
[APPLAUSE]

05:44.812 --> 05:46.547
MAN: Then the water
shall become a flood

05:48.015 --> 05:49.082
and destroy all flesh.

05:51.785 --> 05:53.086
And the bow
shall be in the cloud,

05:55.456 --> 05:57.958
and I will look upon it,
and I will remember

06:00.561 --> 06:02.029
the everlasting covenant

06:03.096 --> 06:05.833
between God
and every living creature.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.102
Of all flesh
that is upon the earth.

06:11.104 --> 06:12.840
And that's what we have here.

06:14.608 --> 06:15.909
Our town is dying.

06:17.978 --> 06:21.615
HARLAN: I have seen
the concrete
monument.

06:23.016 --> 06:26.386
The headstone
for the town for Northfork.

06:29.022 --> 06:31.158
This dam gate will close.

06:32.926 --> 06:35.563
The water will rise
over the plains,

06:36.764 --> 06:37.998
and cover our businesses,

06:40.233 --> 06:41.134
our homes,

06:43.837 --> 06:44.872
and our well-being.

06:48.642 --> 06:50.043
HARLAN:
We have lost Northfork.

06:53.046 --> 06:54.915
We'll be losing our dear son.

06:58.051 --> 07:01.021
But we will gain the hope,

07:01.922 --> 07:02.956
the courage,

07:04.592 --> 07:07.528
to move to
a higher ground.

07:18.005 --> 07:19.673
We're all angels.

07:22.543 --> 07:23.443
It is what we do

07:23.911 --> 07:24.945
with our wings

07:27.114 --> 07:28.181
that separates us.

08:28.108 --> 08:29.142
BOY: What are we waiting for?

08:56.704 --> 08:57.571
[DOOR CREAKS OPEN]

09:37.344 --> 09:38.178
[DOOR OPENS]

09:41.348 --> 09:43.083
Well, Mr. and Mrs. Hadfield.

09:46.787 --> 09:48.088
Father, his health
isn't getting any better.

09:49.256 --> 09:50.057
Rose has had to stay
by his bed.

09:52.059 --> 09:53.627
All the doctors
have left Northfork.

09:58.899 --> 09:59.800
You're returning him then?

10:01.134 --> 10:02.102
HADFIELD: He's a very
ill child.

10:03.270 --> 10:04.772
We cannot make the journey
with him in this condition.

10:06.306 --> 10:08.141
ROSE: We apologize, Father.
[KETTLE WHISTLING]

10:09.309 --> 10:11.078
We appreciate your honesty,

10:12.345 --> 10:14.081
and will ask for forgiveness.

10:14.414 --> 10:15.348
Forgiveness?

10:16.083 --> 10:17.084
Let us be honest, Father.

10:17.117 --> 10:18.218
You gave us a sick child.

10:20.320 --> 10:21.822
I gave you an angel.

10:23.190 --> 10:24.124
You're misunderstanding us.

10:26.226 --> 10:27.227
ROSE: We love Irwin.

10:31.331 --> 10:33.633
Halo home is deeply regretful

10:35.936 --> 10:36.837
about the grief

10:37.671 --> 10:39.239
Irwin has brought
to your family.

10:42.375 --> 10:43.811
God bless.

10:43.844 --> 10:44.712
Have a nice journey.

10:45.145 --> 10:46.246
[ROSE SOBS]

10:51.719 --> 10:52.652
[DOOR OPENS]

10:55.789 --> 10:56.423
[DOOR CLOSES]

10:58.491 --> 10:59.392
[KETTLE WHISTLING]

11:00.994 --> 11:01.862
[DOOR CLOSES]

11:39.900 --> 11:40.768
This is wrong.

11:42.069 --> 11:43.170
This is just downright wrong.

11:46.206 --> 11:47.207
When did you get this letter?

11:48.375 --> 11:49.342
I received the final
notice yesterday.

11:53.313 --> 11:54.748
I don't like this damned cake.

11:57.084 --> 11:57.918
This is wrong on every level.

12:01.989 --> 12:02.923
[SIGHING] Yeah.

12:04.792 --> 12:05.759
[TAPPING]

12:13.033 --> 12:13.867
[CUP CLANKING SOFTLY]

12:37.925 --> 12:38.926
Where did my parents go?

12:43.130 --> 12:44.231
[SIGHS]

12:46.299 --> 12:48.268
We don't wanna go
where they're going.

12:53.240 --> 12:54.341
You rest now.

13:13.293 --> 13:14.895
Father, everybody's leaving.

13:18.265 --> 13:19.299
Oh, I know.

13:20.267 --> 13:21.334
I know.

13:27.074 --> 13:27.875
Oh, let's stay here.

13:29.209 --> 13:30.343
Hmm?

13:31.244 --> 13:32.312
Huh?

15:00.133 --> 15:00.968
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

15:07.140 --> 15:08.008
You're the caretaker?

15:13.313 --> 15:14.414
Yes?

15:16.083 --> 15:16.984
Cookie takes care of the yard.

15:20.687 --> 15:21.588
[SIGHS]

15:34.167 --> 15:35.002
Maybe you can help me?

15:43.676 --> 15:44.677
Who are you looking for?

15:48.248 --> 15:49.116
A relative.

15:58.291 --> 15:59.159
Hold still.

16:48.441 --> 16:49.242
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

16:59.219 --> 17:00.120
[SIGHS]

17:07.527 --> 17:08.494
[CAR DOOR OPENING]

17:10.630 --> 17:11.763
[CAR DOORS SLAMMING SHUT]

17:22.675 --> 17:25.678
Marvin, Matt, Eddie, Arnold.

17:26.646 --> 17:27.814
Walter, Willis,

17:28.648 --> 17:30.083
Eddie, Arnold.

17:31.218 --> 17:34.221
Walter, Willis, Eddie, Arnold.

17:35.522 --> 17:38.658
Walter, Willis, Marvin, Matt.

17:39.626 --> 17:41.661
Marvin, Matt, Walter,

17:42.695 --> 17:43.663
Willis.

17:44.664 --> 17:46.299
Marvin, Matt,

17:47.367 --> 17:48.801
Eddie, Arnold.

18:17.430 --> 18:18.831
Bye-bye. See you.

18:18.865 --> 18:20.400
MARVIN: Anybody voted for him

18:20.433 --> 18:21.601
voted themselves
right out of Northfork.

18:27.574 --> 18:28.375
Have a good journey.

18:30.710 --> 18:32.212
Nice concrete cork.

18:32.245 --> 18:33.112
[MOTOR HUMS]

18:34.481 --> 18:35.582
[WHIRRING]

19:01.408 --> 19:03.210
RUDOLPH: I have done
countless evacs.

19:05.612 --> 19:07.146
And as long as
I've been doing this job,

19:08.715 --> 19:10.350
it has never come down
to 48 hours before.

19:10.983 --> 19:12.151
That's two days.

19:12.185 --> 19:14.287
And by the time I'm through
with you, it's gonna be 47.

19:14.321 --> 19:14.921
So you'd better listen up.

19:15.822 --> 19:17.224
And remember
one very important thing.

19:18.525 --> 19:19.926
Despite the tertiary
inconveniences

19:19.959 --> 19:21.194
we're putting
these people through,

19:22.729 --> 19:23.730
we're giving them new power.

19:25.898 --> 19:26.766
All right?

19:28.435 --> 19:29.369
Matt. [SIGHS]

19:29.936 --> 19:30.870
Marvin.

19:35.775 --> 19:37.744
Please go pay a visit
to the Youngs.

19:44.651 --> 19:45.918
[SIGHING] Eddie, Arnold.

19:49.922 --> 19:50.823
Arnold.

19:55.795 --> 19:57.430
I want you to get down
to Hungry Horse Road,

19:57.464 --> 19:59.266
and I want you to nail Jigger,
do you understand?

20:00.500 --> 20:01.434
You betcha.

20:03.870 --> 20:06.506
Now, you can't go into this
treating it like

20:06.539 --> 20:08.541
you're throwing out
homesteaders,

20:08.575 --> 20:10.477
poor old homesteaders.

20:10.510 --> 20:11.778
Look at it like you're saving

20:11.811 --> 20:13.613
some poor dumb son of
a bitch from drowning...

20:13.646 --> 20:14.681
Mr. Rudolph.

20:16.549 --> 20:17.417
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:18.651 --> 20:19.452
It says here that, uh,

20:21.020 --> 20:23.690
there has been some previous
attempts at evacuation.

20:27.460 --> 20:28.395
[SIGHS]

20:32.665 --> 20:33.666
RUDOLPH: Walter,

20:33.700 --> 20:34.734
Willis.

20:37.437 --> 20:38.705
Stallings. Highway 93.

20:41.841 --> 20:44.777
Remember, the one single
most important thing.

20:44.811 --> 20:45.978
It is not our business

20:46.846 --> 20:47.847
to tell anybody else theirs.

20:49.449 --> 20:52.685
You just come in like
you're their guardian angel.

20:52.719 --> 20:54.821
You give them wings
and then move them up
on to higher ground.

20:56.423 --> 20:56.989
Good luck now, gentlemen.

21:08.735 --> 21:09.736
[SLIDE PROJECTOR CLICKS]

21:10.970 --> 21:12.439
HARLAN: In the early 1800's,

21:13.406 --> 21:15.508
European settlers
named Northfork

21:17.043 --> 21:19.512
after the river
that embraced their town.

21:26.018 --> 21:28.321
Word traveled
throughout the world

21:29.689 --> 21:32.024
that angels roamed
these plains

21:33.626 --> 21:34.527
like bison.

21:38.531 --> 21:39.766
I find the humor
quite parched.

21:41.768 --> 21:43.035
Nineteenth century.

21:43.936 --> 21:44.971
A remarkable piece.

21:49.609 --> 21:51.077
Artist used the finest oils.

21:52.011 --> 21:52.912
[SNIFFS]

21:53.880 --> 21:54.914
Organic pigments.

21:56.683 --> 21:57.550
Magnificent.

21:59.886 --> 22:02.389
The artist has
a religious vocabulary.

22:04.657 --> 22:06.793
He used the luxuriantly
white wings of the swan.

22:08.094 --> 22:11.030
Fascinating representation
of the angelic messenger.

22:13.132 --> 22:14.000
Lovely bird.

22:15.768 --> 22:16.569
If I do recall correctly,

22:17.837 --> 22:19.939
the Celts employed
the majestic swan

22:21.741 --> 22:22.875
as their sacred symbol,

22:24.411 --> 22:25.845
and messenger
to the other world.

22:29.749 --> 22:32.419
Their link that existed
between the realm of
their gods,

22:33.486 --> 22:34.887
and the realm of humans.

22:36.823 --> 22:37.890
Very relatable.

22:39.058 --> 22:40.560
I can only speculate...
[SQUEAKING]

22:45.064 --> 22:48.701
That the man with swan wings,
or in this painting,

22:48.735 --> 22:50.903
the wild bird man,
is a creation

22:53.105 --> 22:54.507
of the overtaking
by Christianity.

22:56.676 --> 22:57.944
Bless the imagination.

