25:50.282 --> 25:53.686
every town,
you go scurrying off
looking for offspring.

25:55.287 --> 25:56.222
Wait.

26:47.406 --> 26:48.340
[THUD]

28:49.528 --> 28:50.429
[PLINKING]

28:58.304 --> 28:59.471
[RATTLING]

29:06.913 --> 29:07.780
[PLINKING]

29:54.193 --> 29:55.027
Would you like a cup of tea?

30:05.004 --> 30:05.838
One lump or two?

30:10.109 --> 30:11.043
My name is Cup of Tea.

30:13.579 --> 30:14.981
To my right,

30:15.014 --> 30:17.049
as you may already know,
is Flower Hercules.

30:18.951 --> 30:19.919
To my left, Cod.

30:21.320 --> 30:22.354
And behind us all,

30:23.489 --> 30:26.058
but in front of you, Happy.

30:30.897 --> 30:31.563
And you are?

30:32.564 --> 30:33.499
Irwin.

30:34.300 --> 30:35.401
Hello, Irwin.

30:37.403 --> 30:38.504
And your surname?

30:39.671 --> 30:40.372
Sir Irwin.

30:42.541 --> 30:47.313
Well, Sir Irwin
of Northfork,

30:47.346 --> 30:49.581
my family and I
have traveled a long way.

30:51.517 --> 30:53.886
And we are having trouble
finding a loved one.

30:54.620 --> 30:55.988
Are you familiar
with the unknown angel?

30:56.588 --> 30:57.456
Yes.

30:58.190 --> 30:59.959
Now.

30:59.992 --> 31:01.593
This is where we can be
of help to each other.

31:06.098 --> 31:06.966
What could we offer you?

31:08.334 --> 31:09.601
When you leave,
just take me with you.

31:10.136 --> 31:11.470
[SCOFFS] No.

31:12.204 --> 31:13.372
Never.

31:14.106 --> 31:15.307
We do not take children.

31:15.341 --> 31:16.976
Then I can't help you.

31:17.009 --> 31:17.609
[STERNLY] Now, Sir Irwin.

31:20.412 --> 31:21.413
You're being unreasonable.

31:22.414 --> 31:24.083
Where we're going,
we can't take you with us.

31:25.117 --> 31:26.352
Then take me 1,000 miles.

31:27.987 --> 31:30.456
One thousand miles in
anybody's book is a long way.

31:35.561 --> 31:37.329
How about 100 miles?

31:37.363 --> 31:38.965
One thousand.
Two hundred.

31:38.998 --> 31:40.599
One thousand.
One thousand.
Three hundred.

31:40.632 --> 31:42.434
Four hundred, and that's it.

31:42.468 --> 31:43.502
[STUBBORNLY] One thousand,
and that's it.

31:48.374 --> 31:49.375
Do you know how far that is?

31:52.011 --> 31:56.415
One thousand miles
is a far, far, faraway place.

32:04.090 --> 32:05.457
Five hundred miles.

32:05.491 --> 32:06.558
IRWIN: One thousand.
All right.

32:08.160 --> 32:10.229
We'll take you
1,000 miles

32:10.262 --> 32:11.063
if you bring us
the unknown angel.

32:14.200 --> 32:15.101
In the morning?

32:15.667 --> 32:16.668
Deal?

32:21.107 --> 32:22.074
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

